President Obama and President Karzai of Afghanistan held a video conference to discuss various topics, including the security situation in Afghanistan, U.S.-Afghan Strategic Partnership negotiations, Afghan-led reconciliation, and regional matters. They acknowledged progress in concluding a Strategic Partnership that respects Afghan sovereignty and addresses transition requirements. President Karzai provided updates on reconciliation talks. Both leaders agreed to maintain a partnership based on mutual respect and to stay in close communication leading up to the NATO Summit in Chicago.